  "prompt": "Why was Twitter successful?",
  "response": "Twitter was successful for several key reasons:\n\n1. Simplicity\n- Short 140/280 character limit\n- Easy to use platform\n- Quick and concise communication\n\n2. Real-time information\n- Instant updates on breaking news\n- Live event commentary\n- Rapid sharing of information\n\n3. Accessibility\n- Free to use\n- Available on multiple devices\n- Low barrier to entry\n\n4. Celebrity and public figure engagement\n- Politicians, celebrities, athletes used platform\n- Direct interaction with followers\n- Increased platform visibility\n\n5. Hashtag innovation\n- Allowed topic tracking\n- Enabled trending conversations\n- Made content discoverable\n\n6. Global reach\n- Accessible worldwide\n- Multilingual support\n- Connected people across geographies\n\n7. Network effects\n- More users attracted more users\n- Easy to follow and be followed\n- Viral content potential\n\n8. Mobile-friendly design\n- Early mobile app adoption\n- Optimized for smartphone use\n- Convenient on-the-go communication\n\n9. Cultural relevance\n- Became a digital public square\n- Platform for social movements\n- Shaped online discourse\n\nThese factors combined to make Twitter a unique and influential social media platform during its peak years.",
